ğŸ§® Notes on Tracker Calculations
Block Hours Remaining (Column I):
This value can go negative to indicate overage.
If a client uses more hours than they have available, the remaining value will show a negative balance.
Formulas auto-fill from Row 2 whenever a new row is added via script.

âš ï¸ Reminder:
The Client Directory is the single source of truth for all automation. Make sure client names, plan types, and statuses are accurate before running scripts.

ğŸ§° Best Practice:
Always use the menu options under â€œClient Toolsâ€ to add or update clients. Avoid inserting or editing rows manually in the Master Tracker, as this can break formulas and automation links.

ğŸ•“ If the New Client Purchased Support Hours
1. Enter the purchased block hours in the appropriate column in the Master Tracker.
2. Ensure the block hours are correctly reflected in the Block Hours Remaining column.
3. Confirm that formulas auto-fill correctly and the clientâ€™s block hour balance updates.
4. Verify that monthly doc generation and block hour syncing include the new block hours.
5. Open the **Block History** tab and record the new support block purchase there as well. This keeps historical records consistent and ensures proper tracking of all purchased blocks.
